Job highlights
Experience with AWS services, Terraform, and Python (or Java) for cloud solutions
Design and support cloud-based contact center solutions, develop infrastructure as code, and manage CI/CD pipelines
--------------
Job description
Role & responsibilities


• Design, implement, and support cloud-based contact center solutions using Amazon Connect and AWS services.
• Develop and maintain infrastructure as code using Terraform for automated cloud resource provisioning.
• Build, deploy, and optimize applications and integrations using Python (or Java) within the AWS ecosystem.
• Engineer and manage Amazon Connect environments, including configuration of IAM, Lex, Lambda, KMS, S3, and Kinesis.
• Create and maintain CI/CD pipelines using Jenkins/Jules and manage code repositories with Git/Bitbucket.
• Rapidly prototype proof-of-concept solutions and scale them to production-ready systems.
• Monitor, debug, and provide production support for large-scale environments using tools such as Splunk, Datadog, and CloudWatch.
• Implement and support RESTful APIs for contact center integrations and automation.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver secure, scalable, and resilient voice solutions.


Role: IT Infrastructure Services - Other
Industry Type: Investment Banking / Venture Capital / Private Equity
Department: IT & Information Security
Employment Type: Full Time, Temporary/Contractual
Role Category: IT Infrastructure Services
